WEBVTT

00:00.140 --> 00:01.776
<i>Previously, on "Bitten"...</i>

00:01.777 --> 00:03.593
Be careful out there.

00:05.163 --> 00:06.487
(Snarling)

00:06.488 --> 00:09.886
Whoever this is, they broke a cardinal
rule by killing a human for sport.

00:09.887 --> 00:12.722
- We'll deal with this as a Pack.
- The Pack needs you.

00:12.793 --> 00:15.691
You're going to have to do better
than that if we're tracking a Mutt.

00:15.692 --> 00:17.222
Miss you, too.

00:17.223 --> 00:19.231
Elena: I have people who
like to know where I am.

00:19.233 --> 00:22.081
- People or person?
- It's not as if you care.

00:22.571 --> 00:24.170
(Growl)
(Scream)

00:24.172 --> 00:27.239
Elena: Another killing.
It almost smells newly turned.

00:27.241 --> 00:28.641
You're gonna want to see this.

00:28.643 --> 00:31.310
- What is it?
- He's just a child.

00:37.116 --> 00:40.930
Elena: This kill, it's the same scent
as the Mutt from the flophouse.

00:40.932 --> 00:43.166
It's the same one that
killed the girl before.

00:43.168 --> 00:46.081
And now a young boy.
This has got to stop.

00:46.391 --> 00:47.791
What are you doing?

00:47.793 --> 00:51.094
He dumped him here to put a target
on our backs. We have to move him.

00:51.096 --> 00:53.163
(High-pitched ring)
(Distant men's voices)

00:53.165 --> 00:55.013
There's hunters
on our property.

00:55.733 --> 00:58.268
(Panting)

00:58.270 --> 00:59.846
He's got the scent.

01:00.234 --> 01:02.144
Trespassing won't matter
if they find this.

01:02.145 --> 01:04.241
Nick, help me
move him.

01:04.242 --> 01:05.975
No, leave the
body there.

01:05.977 --> 01:07.777
If they find a body, we'll
be overrun with police.

01:07.779 --> 01:11.047
It's gonna be a lot worse if
they catch us trying to cover this up.

01:11.049 --> 01:13.516
(Continued shouts)

01:20.758 --> 01:24.084
My god... It's a kid.

01:24.428 --> 01:27.963
- What the hell did you people do?
- We had nothing to do with this.

01:30.634 --> 01:32.468
It's the Richardson boy.

01:32.470 --> 01:34.617
We just found the body. I was
about to call the police.

01:34.618 --> 01:37.963
- Looks like another wolf attack.
- Yeah? We'll let the Sheriff decide that.

01:37.964 --> 01:41.332
In the meantime, we'll stick around, make
sure no one messes with the evidence.

01:41.334 --> 01:43.968
Believe me, we have no intention
of tampering with evidence.

01:43.970 --> 01:46.962
The best thing is for everybody
to just back away from the boy's body.

01:46.963 --> 01:48.163
We will wait
for the police.

01:48.164 --> 01:50.431
Look, I don't know what you
people are doing out here,

01:50.433 --> 01:53.067
but this is the second wolf
kill in a couple of days

01:53.068 --> 01:55.302
and you've got goddamn tracks
all over your property.

01:55.303 --> 01:56.670
It's private
property.

01:56.672 --> 01:59.807
Maybe you'd like to explain what
the Richardson boy is doing out here.

01:59.809 --> 02:00.762
Braxton...

02:00.763 --> 02:03.132
Clay: You're implying what's
happened here is our fault?

02:03.134 --> 02:05.941
Dead body, your property:
you do the math.

02:05.942 --> 02:08.965
We have nothing to do with this.
Anybody who thinks that is a fool.

02:08.966 --> 02:11.167
- You're calling me a fool?
- Easy...

02:11.326 --> 02:13.476
Everybody just
calm down now.

02:13.478 --> 02:16.045
(Barking)

02:16.047 --> 02:18.590
- Man: Calm down, calm down!
- Blue! Stop!

02:18.591 --> 02:20.524
It's time
for you to go.

02:20.525 --> 02:22.459
(Click)

02:22.569 --> 02:24.469
(Grunt) Hey, what the hell?

02:24.470 --> 02:26.708
(Groaning)
(Panting)

02:26.709 --> 02:29.076
What the hell? Blue!

02:29.324 --> 02:34.359
Next time you pop the safety off your
gun, I'm gonna give you reason to use it.

02:35.443 --> 02:37.560
That's enough.

02:37.967 --> 02:39.952
Enough.

02:40.523 --> 02:44.263
The most important thing is to do right
by this boy and his family now.

02:45.344 --> 02:46.643
Antonio and Nick,

02:46.645 --> 02:49.432
escort these gentlemen to the front
gate and you wait for the sheriff.

02:49.433 --> 02:50.683
- Blue!
- Hey, come...

02:50.684 --> 02:54.095
Braxton! The damn dog
will find his own way home.

02:58.059 --> 02:59.892
(Spit)

03:00.137 --> 03:03.211
Braxton: We'll see what the sheriff
has to say about this.

03:04.057 --> 03:06.355
Man: Come on, let's
get out of here.

03:07.438 --> 03:09.405
Who would do this
to a child?

03:09.610 --> 03:11.309
That's what we have
to find out.

03:14.914 --> 03:16.882
(Dialling beeps)

03:18.282 --> 03:21.035
Sheriff Morgan?
This is Jeremy Danvers.

03:21.329 --> 03:23.192
There's been
another killing.

03:25.457 --> 03:34.457
( ♪ )

