04:02.601 --> 04:04.735
Goading the dog
was very clever, Elena.

04:04.736 --> 04:07.131
That dog could
have attacked you.

04:07.169 --> 04:09.962
You act like I've never
been bitten before.

04:10.321 --> 04:13.389
- How ironic.
- If you're angry at me, come at me.

04:13.390 --> 04:15.568
- Right at me. Don't talk around it.
- That's enough.

04:15.569 --> 04:18.767
- Pete: The hunters are off the property.
- For now, anyway.

04:18.769 --> 04:22.065
At the rate that this Mutt's going,
that's not going to last for very long.

04:22.065 --> 04:24.532
The first kill was on
the outskirts of town,

04:24.533 --> 04:27.461
the second one was dropped
in our backyard, what's his plan?

04:27.462 --> 04:30.845
He's drawing attention to us and
he's upped the stakes by killing a kid.

04:30.846 --> 04:33.730
He's escalating. He's turning
up the heat, bit by bit.

04:33.731 --> 04:34.973
But why?

04:34.974 --> 04:38.635
The psychological damage to the recently
bitten Mutt is unpredictable.

04:38.636 --> 04:40.712
Yeah, except for the fact
that he's targeting us.

04:40.713 --> 04:42.715
Or he just likes to kill
women and children

04:42.717 --> 04:44.383
and wants to flaunt
it in our territory.

04:44.385 --> 04:47.930
Sheriff just arrived.
She's heading out to see the body.

04:47.931 --> 04:49.598
Look...

04:49.822 --> 04:52.188
A Mutt killed a kid.

04:52.793 --> 04:54.660
I'll stay
until we find him.

04:56.229 --> 04:57.796
Okay.

04:57.798 --> 05:00.599
Antonio, you and I will
deal with Sheriff Morgan.

05:00.601 --> 05:03.992
Elena... You and Clay
go into town.

05:03.993 --> 05:06.105
See if you can pick up
the scent of the Mutt.

05:06.107 --> 05:07.980
Start with the bars.

05:08.442 --> 05:12.117
- I'll be ready in five minutes.
- I want him alive.

05:12.557 --> 05:15.469
I need to know who turned him
before we mete out punishment.

05:15.470 --> 05:18.688
There is someone out there who knows
the Mutt rumour mill better than us.

05:18.689 --> 05:21.620
- Karl Marsten.
- If he's even in the country.

05:21.622 --> 05:23.206
Find out,
Nick.

05:23.300 --> 05:26.891
If he is, I want you and Logan
to track him down and see what he knows.

05:26.963 --> 05:28.487
Got it.

05:29.929 --> 05:33.012
Well, hey, I'll just stick around
here and do some sweeping up.

05:33.013 --> 05:34.695
I can clean out the
fireplace, too if...

05:34.696 --> 05:37.668
Pete, you, go
with Nick and Logan.

05:37.670 --> 05:40.705
A little show of force is always
useful with Karl Marsten.

05:40.707 --> 05:43.140
A show of force. Hear that?
(Growl)

05:43.510 --> 05:46.010
Oh, it's so nice not being
the youngest around here...

05:46.012 --> 05:47.463
Give me a minute.

05:47.553 --> 05:49.653
Come outside with
me for a second.

05:49.654 --> 05:51.260
Stay.

06:00.592 --> 06:02.226
(Sigh)

06:06.316 --> 06:08.517
This came for you today.

06:08.934 --> 06:12.469
Someone cares enough to know
that these are your favourite flowers.

06:16.315 --> 06:18.183
So is it serious?

06:20.886 --> 06:24.733
- Serious enough.
- To keep it from me.

06:25.626 --> 06:29.457
I know how you feel about long-term
relationships with humans.

06:30.729 --> 06:33.854
You also know how
much I trust you.

06:34.134 --> 06:36.646
You don't have to
manage me, Elena.

06:37.631 --> 06:41.778
I don't want you to keep secrets
about Philip or anything else.

06:42.114 --> 06:43.688
You know his name.

06:43.689 --> 06:45.678
- He signed the card.
- Right.

06:45.680 --> 06:47.046
(Laugh)

06:47.048 --> 06:49.181
Very nice of him
to send flowers.

06:51.451 --> 06:55.410
(Sigh) Yeah... He's one
of the good ones, you know.

06:56.483 --> 06:58.283
I hate lying to him.

07:00.260 --> 07:04.611
Our whole existence hinges
on the lies we tell humans.

07:05.329 --> 07:07.506
And sometimes...

07:08.645 --> 07:11.517
We have to keep some
truths from our own too.

07:14.205 --> 07:16.841
We can't hide these
out here forever.

07:18.621 --> 07:21.155
Do you think that
I should get rid of them?

07:21.314 --> 07:30.314
( ♪ )

07:38.807 --> 07:41.832
- Elena: (On phone) <i>I got the flowers.</i>
- They reached you. Good.

07:41.834 --> 07:44.807
I didn't know where to send them,
but the florist knew the Danvers name.

07:44.808 --> 07:46.967
Well, they're beautiful.
But you didn't have to.

07:46.968 --> 07:50.260
Well, making my girlfriend feel better
is actually something I have to do.

07:50.261 --> 07:52.187
- It's the law.
- Oh, really?

07:52.188 --> 07:54.859
Well, I guess that makes you an
upstanding citizen, doesn't it?

07:54.893 --> 07:56.926
Philip: (On phone) <i>Well,
sometimes I feel like a rebel.</i>

07:56.928 --> 07:58.794
Like right now,
I'm not wearing any pants.

07:58.796 --> 08:01.931
Are you showing off for the old lady
with the binoculars, or what?

08:01.933 --> 08:03.900
<i>Yep. She's getting</i>
<i>a hell of a show.</i>

08:03.902 --> 08:07.359
Any time now she's gonna
get the no-pants dance.

08:07.384 --> 08:10.473
Wow. Okay, what else
do you have in store?

08:10.475 --> 08:11.774
(High-pitched ring)

08:11.776 --> 08:15.578
Elena:
(Muffled laughter, chatter)

08:17.046 --> 08:19.682
(Engine ignition)
(♪ on radio)

08:19.684 --> 08:28.684
( ♪ )

08:29.878 --> 08:32.378
(On radio)
<i>♪ I remember that day ♪</i>

08:32.379 --> 08:34.046
<i>♪ In Memphis town ♪</i>

08:34.047 --> 08:36.147
<i>♪ I was down on my luck ♪</i>

08:36.148 --> 08:38.181
<i>♪ I was hanging around ♪</i>

08:38.335 --> 08:42.537
<i>♪ The record company called
"Not sending any money" ♪</i>

08:42.539 --> 08:46.508
<i>♪ But I was so drunk
that I didn't even care ♪</i>

08:46.510 --> 08:55.510
( ♪ )

09:09.485 --> 09:13.301
Word's spreading through town.
They've upped the bounty on the wolf.

09:13.303 --> 09:15.256
I thought that hunting
wolves was illegal.

09:15.257 --> 09:17.370
It is, but now I've
got two kids in town

09:17.372 --> 09:19.540
saying they've seen one
roaming the streets.

09:19.542 --> 09:22.278
Before this gets any worse,
I'd rather have a slap on the wrist

09:22.304 --> 09:24.967
from Wildlife Control than see
another dead body turn up.

09:24.968 --> 09:27.047
Tense nerves and firearms

09:27.049 --> 09:29.470
just doesn't seem to be
the safest combination, Sheriff.

09:29.471 --> 09:31.971
I hear you.
But people want justice.

09:32.126 --> 09:34.854
Killing that wolf might just
give them the closure they need.

09:34.856 --> 09:37.324
Antonio: Everyone's
back up at the house.

09:37.326 --> 09:39.225
They're pretty
shaken up.

09:39.227 --> 09:41.661
How is it you all found
this boy together?

09:41.663 --> 09:44.826
Well, we were out for a walk
and that's when we s...

09:45.033 --> 09:46.399
That's when we saw him.

09:46.401 --> 09:49.401
You have a lot of problems with kids
trespassing on your property?

09:49.403 --> 09:52.581
Antonio: Not usually.
The occasional party in the woods.

09:52.582 --> 09:56.958
- Teenagers.
- I have a vague memory being one.

09:57.287 --> 10:00.088
Any idea why an 11-year-old
boy would even be out here?

10:00.089 --> 10:01.922
Absolutely none.

10:01.923 --> 10:04.613
Sheriff, the coroner
would like a word.

10:04.666 --> 10:06.416
Gentlemen.

10:07.025 --> 10:10.312
I'm not looking forward to notifying
the family, I'll tell you that.

10:10.313 --> 10:12.630
What's your take on things?

10:12.958 --> 10:15.886
Better we find this Mutt
before she does.

10:16.739 --> 10:19.529
- Mr. Williams.
- James, please.

10:19.531 --> 10:22.851
- Thank you for meeting me here.
- It's a little strange.

10:22.852 --> 10:25.705
I... usually give
presentations in board rooms.

10:25.706 --> 10:28.006
I couldn't bring
this to the office.

10:28.008 --> 10:30.876
There's a power struggle going
on with my board of directors.

10:30.878 --> 10:33.578
Some want to scale
back our assets,

10:33.701 --> 10:37.081
- I want to expand.
- Into vodka.

10:37.405 --> 10:39.986
I've found one of Estonia's
best-kept secrets.

10:40.042 --> 10:43.344
A little-known family
operation called Viljandi.

10:43.346 --> 10:46.547
And they make the finest small
batch vodka in the Balkans.

10:46.549 --> 10:48.796
(Laugh) Sounds like a good get.

10:49.102 --> 10:51.824
And the Cassie Awards make
you a good get as well.

10:51.844 --> 10:53.785
I vetted your portfolio.

10:53.786 --> 10:57.223
And I think you're the right person to
help me position the vodka to my board.

10:57.225 --> 11:00.718
Your job is to convince them
that it will sell in North America.

11:01.092 --> 11:02.725
Give me your thoughts.

11:04.509 --> 11:07.076
(Church bells tolling)

11:07.077 --> 11:16.077
( ♪ )

11:17.466 --> 11:19.934
I never realized Bear
Valley had so many bars.

11:19.936 --> 11:22.136
And so far, our Mutt's
been to all of them.

11:22.138 --> 11:24.138
Yeah, well it's easy
hunting grounds.

11:25.947 --> 11:30.216
But his scent's still too faint.
Couple days old at least.

11:30.312 --> 11:32.178
There's nothing new
in the air but...

11:32.180 --> 11:35.682
Rotten tomatoes, milk
that's about to turn...

11:35.684 --> 11:39.285
- (Sniff) Diesel, sweat...
- Lilacs.

11:41.668 --> 11:43.623
How long you been holding
that one in, Clay?

11:43.625 --> 11:45.631
Long as I could.

11:46.793 --> 11:48.827
Look...

11:48.828 --> 11:51.931
I had to come up with an excuse
for leaving Toronto so abruptly.

11:51.933 --> 11:54.968
So I said that my cousin
got in a car accident.

11:54.970 --> 11:59.405
- Hence the flowers.
- I'd imagine that's difficult.

11:59.407 --> 12:01.507
Having to come up
with excuses.

12:01.509 --> 12:03.935
Kind of like what
I'm doing with you right now?

12:03.936 --> 12:07.204
That's the thing...
You shouldn't have to, with me.

12:09.070 --> 12:12.072
Hunter: Surprised to see
you two in town.

12:12.175 --> 12:14.699
Nothing like a little
Bear Valley hospitality.

12:15.932 --> 12:17.966
Just come from
Bill Richardson's.

12:17.967 --> 12:20.092
He runs the gas station on
the way out to your place.

12:20.094 --> 12:21.960
I'm sure you've filled up
there a bunch of times.

12:21.962 --> 12:23.242
We have.

12:23.243 --> 12:27.165
Well, that kid we found on your
property was his grandson.

12:27.167 --> 12:30.335
So you're probably going to want to find
a new place to fill up for a while.

12:30.337 --> 12:34.138
Look, we had nothing
to do with his death.

12:34.140 --> 12:36.937
Don't you think that
we feel horrible too?

12:36.964 --> 12:38.797
We saw the paw prints.

12:38.799 --> 12:42.617
Braxton's convinced that there's
a wolf roaming around on your property

12:42.618 --> 12:44.235
and you ain't doing
much to stop it.

12:44.250 --> 12:47.780
- That's not the case.
- Well, his dog's still missing.

12:47.898 --> 12:51.599
And if that wolf gets Blue,
blame's going directly on you.

12:51.631 --> 12:55.937
- We'll keep an eye out for Blue, okay?
- And the wolf.

12:55.939 --> 12:58.006
We're all on the
lookout for that.

13:00.809 --> 13:04.226
That boy deserves
justice, I know.

13:13.409 --> 13:14.976
I don't get it.

13:14.978 --> 13:16.844
Some Mutt comes blazing
through Bear Valley,

13:16.846 --> 13:19.360
leaving... behind
three dead bodies,

13:19.361 --> 13:22.930
one specifically left on our
property, and then vanishes.

13:22.932 --> 13:24.259
Why?

13:24.986 --> 13:27.313
Maybe he made his
point and left town?

13:27.336 --> 13:29.699
Or like Logan said,
he's gone mad with the Change.

13:29.700 --> 13:34.233
Yeah, but... he could kill
in any dark corner of the country...

13:34.234 --> 13:37.844
But he's here.
There's a reason.

13:37.846 --> 13:40.313
Those kills are a message.

13:40.315 --> 13:44.037
Then we find him and ask.
Up close and personal.

13:54.027 --> 13:56.095
(Dance ♪)

13:56.097 --> 14:05.097
( ♪ )

14:13.158 --> 14:15.926
Officer: Have you been in touch
with the family yet?

14:15.928 --> 14:18.495
(Indistinct reply
on two-way radio)

14:18.496 --> 14:25.467
( ♪ )

14:25.468 --> 14:27.668
I see you've called in
the reinforcements.

14:27.669 --> 14:30.666
The victim's a child.
Makes everyone move faster.

14:30.667 --> 14:32.400
Even the government.

14:32.563 --> 14:34.362
Those two are
wildlife experts.

14:34.364 --> 14:36.031
What do they think
they're going to find?

14:36.033 --> 14:39.101
Hopefully, an indication of what
kind of animal were dealing with.

14:39.103 --> 14:41.670
Oh... I thought
this was a wolf.

14:41.672 --> 14:44.406
Could be. The boys
aren't so sure.

14:44.408 --> 14:49.214
Something about the size of the prints
and the length of the stride.

14:49.580 --> 14:54.216
I'm not even gonna start guessing.
It'll only add fuel to the rumours.

14:55.791 --> 14:57.237
Could be a
long night.

14:57.238 --> 15:00.422
Well, if you, or any of your colleagues
need anything, don't hesitate to ask.

15:00.424 --> 15:02.980
I appreciate that,
Mr. Danvers.

15:03.057 --> 15:07.972
All we need are some answers, and
we're not gonna stop until we find some.

15:10.375 --> 15:12.795
- No!
- Don't say no.

15:12.802 --> 15:14.802
All these leftovers from
the wedding shower...

15:14.804 --> 15:18.472
I can't possibly eat this by myself.
The cholesterol would kill me.

15:18.474 --> 15:20.672
Oh, so you're slowly going
to kill me instead?

15:20.673 --> 15:24.511
(Laugh) What the hell. I'll eat it.
Pre-celebration.

15:24.512 --> 15:28.080
I just landed a client that's gonna make
me my year if not my entire decade.

15:28.083 --> 15:32.553
So, are you and Elena gonna...
paint the town red tonight?

15:32.555 --> 15:35.222
No, she's off in Upstate
New York with family.

15:35.593 --> 15:39.283
- I thought she didn't have a family.
- Yeah, I just found out myself.

15:40.340 --> 15:45.103
Six months you've been together, and
you're just hearing now about a family?

15:45.104 --> 15:47.890
I'll take the cheese, Mom.
You can keep your advice.

15:47.893 --> 15:50.399
I don't want this one
to break your heart.

15:50.603 --> 15:55.238
I can tell that you're all-in.
Obviously she's not.

15:55.679 --> 15:59.393
She's guarded. She has
a complicated history.

15:59.712 --> 16:03.247
What is so complicated
about being honest?

16:03.248 --> 16:06.044
( ♪ )

16:07.311 --> 16:09.670
Nick: I wanted to show you
guys my new club anyway,

16:09.671 --> 16:12.365
so I thought I'd have Marsten
just come meet us here.

16:12.366 --> 16:16.665
It's a work in progress. I haven't
told my dad I bought the place yet.

16:16.712 --> 16:20.447
And because your investment
acumen is stellar.

16:20.770 --> 16:24.372
I think that was delivered with irony,
but I'm gonna take it as a compliment.

16:24.374 --> 16:26.707
How are those Facebook
shares working for you?

16:26.709 --> 16:29.700
Is there a dislike button for
what happened to those stocks?

16:29.725 --> 16:34.247
You know, I like to think of my financial
past as isolated teaching moments

16:34.249 --> 16:37.014
which have brought me
to where I am today.

16:37.240 --> 16:39.575
How's that
working for you?

16:39.576 --> 16:41.276
Gentlemen.

16:41.645 --> 16:43.025
What do you think?

16:43.026 --> 16:45.746
(Clears throat)
Uhh...

16:45.748 --> 16:48.849
Hot mess
time machine?

16:48.851 --> 16:50.884
Dude, do not tell
your father about this.

16:50.886 --> 16:52.295
(Thud) Ugh.

16:52.296 --> 16:55.690
Nick: Come on, you guys, once
it's reno'd it could be a vision.

16:56.125 --> 16:59.393
You'll like what's
coming our way.

16:59.395 --> 17:00.694
Oh... my God.

17:00.696 --> 17:03.553
- Nicholas.
- Amanda, you look stunning.

17:04.409 --> 17:05.909
I wasn't expecting you.

17:05.911 --> 17:07.611
The carpenters won't be
here for another week.

17:07.613 --> 17:11.038
Just a little bit of business.
Some personal... (Clears throat)

17:12.452 --> 17:16.554
Amanda, meet my old friends.
This is Logan and Peter.

17:16.556 --> 17:18.255
- Pete.
- Pleasure.

17:18.257 --> 17:19.556
Yeah. Hi.

17:19.558 --> 17:21.558
- You're the manager.
- Yeah. Amazing.

17:21.560 --> 17:24.396
Amanda here is gonna
overhaul the place for me.

17:24.397 --> 17:27.387
Oh. Well, at least you have the good
sense to hire someone with taste.

17:27.387 --> 17:29.574
Nick:
Hey, I have taste, okay?

17:29.660 --> 17:30.860
(Clears throat)

17:33.172 --> 17:37.247
- How'd Marsten get here so fast?
- Time to rock and roll, boys.

17:37.540 --> 17:39.077
Let's play it cool.

17:40.412 --> 17:42.447
Clay: GPS says
this is the place.

17:42.449 --> 17:45.016
(Muffled dance ♪)

17:45.018 --> 17:49.621
( ♪ )

17:49.622 --> 17:51.847
- What are you doing?
- I'm going in alone.

17:51.848 --> 17:55.357
- That's not gonna happen.
- Right, 'cause you'll blend in so well.

17:55.358 --> 17:59.395
- That's not what this is about, is it?
- I can handle this, okay?

18:00.166 --> 18:02.333
You're so uptight they'll
think you're a narc.

18:02.335 --> 18:05.069
Okay, look, you have to stop
believing I can't control myself.

18:05.071 --> 18:06.820
It's unfair.

18:07.109 --> 18:08.567
Besides...

18:08.601 --> 18:10.734
We're better when we
have each other's backs.

18:12.811 --> 18:16.920
Okay, but if he's in there, the two
of us going in at the same time...

18:16.921 --> 18:19.874
Yeah, it's liable to spook him.
You're right.

18:20.529 --> 18:24.130
Drive him towards that door.
I'll grab him on the way out.

18:25.588 --> 18:30.059
- That's actually not a terrible plan.
- It's not my first Mutt hunt.

18:33.162 --> 18:35.596
I hoped my hunting
days were over.

18:36.742 --> 18:38.375
But...

18:38.494 --> 18:42.470
Once more into the fray, right?
How do I look?

18:52.445 --> 18:54.714
Now you're perfect.

18:57.018 --> 18:59.586
(Muffled ♪ continues)

18:59.588 --> 19:08.588
( ♪ )

19:08.897 --> 19:10.130
(Engine stops)

19:12.967 --> 19:17.537
A hand-rolled Casanegra.
A man of refined tastes.

19:17.539 --> 19:21.575
Unfortunately, I'm allergic
to cigar smoke, so would you mind...?

19:21.577 --> 19:26.379
Soft approach, appealing to my
obvious class, and a winning smile.

19:26.381 --> 19:31.151
Why ever is a butterfly like you caught
up in a white trash net like this?

19:32.610 --> 19:34.520
You know, honouring
a lady's polite request

19:34.522 --> 19:37.230
is much more
flattering than praise.

19:38.256 --> 19:40.565
Then your wish
is my command.

19:42.452 --> 19:44.487
You called?

19:44.488 --> 19:48.100
If it were for my design advice, I would
suggest starting with a blowtorch.

19:48.102 --> 19:52.251
- Can I get you a drink?
- One part vodka, two parts poison?

19:53.584 --> 19:56.018
We don't have any
bad blood, do we?

19:56.020 --> 19:59.299
Between us?
Of course not.

19:59.957 --> 20:01.724
Let's get to it,
shall we?

20:03.894 --> 20:06.428
(Dance ♪)

20:06.430 --> 20:15.430
( ♪ )

21:11.025 --> 21:13.226
(Eerie high-pitched ring)

21:16.064 --> 21:20.149
- You know who I am?
- I know what you are.

21:20.535 --> 21:22.454
I can smell it.

21:22.771 --> 21:27.151
Seems you and I share something
very special in common.

21:27.375 --> 21:32.086
We couldn't be more different.
You killed three innocent people.

21:32.321 --> 21:35.055
They break so
easily now.

21:35.289 --> 21:36.829
I love this.

21:37.298 --> 21:40.387
What you broke
are the rules.

21:40.388 --> 21:42.557
Killing people
isn't allowed.

21:43.224 --> 21:46.258
You ever see the look in their
eyes when they're about to die?

21:46.260 --> 21:48.694
When they realize
that...

21:48.696 --> 21:50.852
You <i>are</i> death.

21:52.052 --> 21:55.094
I'm not gonna let your rules
get in the way of my fun.

21:57.471 --> 21:59.437
Wrong answer.

21:59.439 --> 22:08.013
( ♪ )

22:08.015 --> 22:09.481
(Grunts)

22:09.483 --> 22:11.984
I don't think you can stop
me getting what I want.

22:11.986 --> 22:15.353
- Back off.
- What if I don't feel like it?

22:16.522 --> 22:20.157
(Grunts of combat)

22:20.159 --> 22:22.026
Ah!
(Groaning)

22:22.028 --> 22:23.327
Feel that?

22:23.329 --> 22:25.897
(Fast heartbeat)

22:25.899 --> 22:29.466
(Retching, grunting)

22:29.468 --> 22:31.335
No, look,
just calm down.

22:31.337 --> 22:33.533
(Grunting)
You'll Change right here!

22:33.534 --> 22:36.664
- Calm the hell down!
- I don't know how!

22:37.776 --> 22:39.009
Come on!

22:39.011 --> 22:41.545
(Grunts of effort)

22:41.547 --> 22:43.613
( ♪ )

22:43.615 --> 22:45.815
Out of the way!
He's going to be sick!

22:48.686 --> 22:51.021
(Panting)

22:51.023 --> 22:52.756
Man:
(Screaming)

22:52.758 --> 22:55.959
( ♪ )

22:55.961 --> 22:58.494
(Distant shouts)

22:58.496 --> 23:07.496
( ♪ )

23:10.975 --> 23:13.509
(Thumping on door)
(Growling)

23:22.147 --> 23:25.682
Nick: You certainly are
an international Mutt of mystery.

23:25.684 --> 23:29.353
Last I heard you were in London, but
yet here you are at a moment's notice.

23:29.355 --> 23:32.256
I'm curious to know what
you're doing in the area.

23:32.258 --> 23:34.558
You think I don't know how
to set up a Google alert?

23:34.560 --> 23:37.493
Wolf attacks in
Upstate New York.

23:37.495 --> 23:41.121
That means something is happening.
I like to be close to the action.

23:41.147 --> 23:43.965
- What have you heard?
- Nothing yet.

23:44.090 --> 23:48.038
But the fact you're asking suggests
that you haven't heard anything either.

23:48.040 --> 23:50.973
(Pool balls clacking) We know
a new Mutt is causing this.

23:50.975 --> 23:52.908
Hm. Very interesting.

23:52.910 --> 23:54.798
What we want to know
is who bit him.

23:54.799 --> 23:57.611
Ah, yes, the million
dollar question.

23:58.524 --> 24:00.450
I could find out.

24:02.240 --> 24:04.341
For a price, I'm sure.

24:04.343 --> 24:06.476
Just some goodwill
from the Pack.

24:06.478 --> 24:09.412
You have something
specific in mind?

24:09.414 --> 24:12.615
I've stuck by your rules.
I'm always on the move.

24:12.617 --> 24:14.860
I've never stayed in
one place for long.

24:16.821 --> 24:20.122
We still don't know
what it is you want.

24:20.124 --> 24:24.284
Just an open mind from Jeremy
on my desire for territory.

24:24.322 --> 24:28.264
Sometimes is nice to have a place
to put your feet up.

24:28.266 --> 24:30.673
I'll find out who bit
your little problem.

24:34.104 --> 24:37.525
Maybe I'll even walk him
up to your front door.

24:41.244 --> 24:43.812
(Thuds against door)
(Clattering)

24:47.684 --> 24:49.017
(Thuds, clattering stop)

24:49.019 --> 24:58.019
( ♪ )

25:16.111 --> 25:18.546
(Screaming)

25:22.785 --> 25:24.886
(Growling)

25:24.888 --> 25:27.121
(Mixed screaming)

25:28.189 --> 25:29.389
Whoa!

25:31.092 --> 25:33.560
Man:
(Screaming)

25:36.898 --> 25:39.366
(Mixed screaming)

25:41.069 --> 25:43.570
(Snarling)
(Screaming)

25:49.681 --> 25:52.813
Look at me! Look at me!
You're gonna be okay.

25:54.348 --> 25:56.850
(Continued screaming)

26:01.019 --> 26:03.156
Why in the hell would a
wolf go into a warehouse

26:03.158 --> 26:04.757
packed with people
and loud music?

26:04.759 --> 26:06.459
It doesn't make
any sense! Damn it.

26:06.461 --> 26:08.094
Sheriff: Call the hospital,
tell them to expect...

26:08.096 --> 26:09.329
I don't what
to expect!

26:09.331 --> 26:11.597
Something big
is going down.

26:11.599 --> 26:13.666
(Sirens wailing)

26:13.668 --> 26:16.569
Sheriff: Do you have any idea how
much carnage we might be looking at?

26:16.571 --> 26:18.637
Our Mutt just made
his next move.

26:18.639 --> 26:20.539
(Panicked screams)

26:20.541 --> 26:22.194
(Grunts of pain)

26:26.145 --> 26:28.647
(Snarling)

26:28.649 --> 26:37.649
( ♪ )

26:50.269 --> 26:52.737
(Screams)

26:55.708 --> 26:58.242
Secure the area,
right now!

27:02.548 --> 27:07.051
(Panicked shouts)

27:13.125 --> 27:14.325
Okay, okay.

27:19.831 --> 27:21.596
Everybody down!

27:22.800 --> 27:24.001
(Whimper)

27:27.405 --> 27:29.840
(Whining)

27:32.243 --> 27:34.177
(Growling)

27:38.783 --> 27:41.151
(Squishing)

27:41.153 --> 27:43.753
(Continued screaming)
(Sirens wailing)

27:52.400 --> 27:54.901
(Police radio chatter)

27:54.903 --> 28:02.943
( ♪ )

28:02.945 --> 28:05.045
Elena, the cops definitely
don't need to find us here.

28:05.047 --> 28:07.856
One guy was still alive when I left.
He was bitten.

28:10.347 --> 28:12.015
This way.

28:17.258 --> 28:19.792
(Shallow breathing,
gasping)

28:21.495 --> 28:23.929
Do you know
where you are?

28:23.931 --> 28:26.198
Hot... I'm hot...

28:26.200 --> 28:28.100
Do you remember
what happened?

28:28.102 --> 28:30.236
- Dog.
- We need to hurry.

28:30.238 --> 28:33.806
(Wincing) I...
I don't feel so good.

28:36.274 --> 28:38.342
You use needles?

28:38.344 --> 28:40.276
Heroin?

28:40.278 --> 28:42.788
- Sometimes.
- Clay, no.

28:43.983 --> 28:45.983
Can you stand?

28:45.985 --> 28:47.250
No...

28:47.252 --> 28:51.454
Clay, we can take him to Stonehaven,
we can put him in the cage.

28:51.456 --> 28:54.825
Clay... listen to me!

28:58.896 --> 29:00.830
(Groaning)

29:02.033 --> 29:04.867
Okay. Come here,
come here.

29:04.869 --> 29:06.469
Shh.

29:06.471 --> 29:08.335
Shh, it's okay.

29:10.241 --> 29:11.707
Don't.

29:11.709 --> 29:14.209
Please... stop.

29:14.211 --> 29:16.646
Shh.

29:19.282 --> 29:21.751
(Grunting)

29:23.687 --> 29:26.187
It's okay, it's okay.

29:34.932 --> 29:38.467
<i>♪ What you got
in store for me? ♪</i>

29:41.271 --> 29:46.307
<i>♪ Keep those eyes closed
Next to me ♪</i>

29:48.477 --> 29:51.012
<i>♪ And I don't want
another... ♪</i>

29:52.247 --> 29:54.716
You didn't have
to kill him.

29:54.718 --> 29:57.552
He was weak.
Habitual drug user.

29:57.554 --> 30:00.055
No way he would've
survived the Change.

30:00.057 --> 30:02.856
I saved him days of agony,
and you know it.

30:04.493 --> 30:06.260
Let's get out of here.

30:06.262 --> 30:14.569
( ♪ )

30:14.883 --> 30:17.349
<i>♪ Warm shadow ♪</i>

30:20.341 --> 30:22.810
<i>♪ Mmm ♪</i>

30:26.247 --> 30:29.416
<i>♪ Warm shadow ♪</i>

30:29.418 --> 30:33.580
<i>♪ Won't you cast
yourself on me ♪</i>

30:34.222 --> 30:38.325
- Pete: So, what do you think?
- He's pretty confident.

30:38.327 --> 30:41.394
Mm-hmm. Already
negotiating a deal.

30:41.396 --> 30:43.530
He clearly knows more
than he's letting on.

30:43.532 --> 30:45.746
Well, holding out on us
isn't a good idea.

30:45.747 --> 30:48.881
Jeremy would bust him a new hole.
I don't think he's that stupid.

30:48.883 --> 30:51.783
He's a sociopath.
He's a con man.

30:51.785 --> 30:54.672
A con man is a sociopath, (cellphone
ringtone) he's just good at hiding it.

30:54.698 --> 30:57.256
Hold up, hold up.
Jeremy, what's happening?

30:57.258 --> 30:59.557
- The Mutt's dead.
- Pete: (On phone) <i>Clay and Elena?</i>

30:59.559 --> 31:02.481
No, they're both safe. They didn't
get a chance to question him.

31:02.482 --> 31:06.265
Okay, well, Marsten
didn't cop to much.

31:06.267 --> 31:08.232
We'll figure that
out eventually.

31:08.234 --> 31:10.435
Listen, you and Logan don't have
to come back to Stonehaven.

31:10.437 --> 31:13.571
- We'll take it from here.
- Okay.

31:13.573 --> 31:15.973
Well, you know
to find me, amigo.

31:15.975 --> 31:17.241
Boom!

31:17.243 --> 31:20.144
Scratch a killer Mutt
off the list of life.

31:20.146 --> 31:21.846
Let me guess.
Clay got him.

31:21.848 --> 31:24.282
All I know is Jeremy
says you and I can go.

31:24.284 --> 31:26.417
I'm going to see if I can
catch the rest of the tour.

31:26.419 --> 31:28.097
I got a lady
waiting on me.

31:29.687 --> 31:31.355
Come on, man.
Hug it out, baby.

31:31.357 --> 31:32.790
Hug it out!

31:32.792 --> 31:34.892
- Hug it like you own it!
- Okay, okay, okay.

31:34.894 --> 31:36.808
- Come on now.
- Okay. (Laugh)

31:36.992 --> 31:39.828
- You.
- No wedgies...

31:41.087 --> 31:42.787
(Grunting)

31:42.788 --> 31:44.059
Agh...

31:44.060 --> 31:45.609
God!

31:45.938 --> 31:47.935
I love you guys.

31:48.091 --> 31:49.625
Huh?

31:49.689 --> 31:51.822
- Nick: Love you too.
- Pete: My boys.

31:53.077 --> 31:55.211
Elena: Clay...

31:55.213 --> 31:58.734
Look, just stop.
Please stop.

31:59.451 --> 32:01.284
I really screwed
up tonight.

32:01.285 --> 32:03.420
- I let the situation get out of hand.
- Listen to me.

32:03.422 --> 32:06.226
The fact he couldn't control his
Change, that's not your fault.

32:06.227 --> 32:08.791
- He was a ticking time bomb...
- You're not listening to me!

32:08.793 --> 32:12.996
I'm the ticking time bomb!
We both are.

32:12.998 --> 32:15.765
Look, we don't think clearly
when we're around one another.

32:15.767 --> 32:17.567
People are dead.

32:17.569 --> 32:20.776
Elena, we stopped him
from killing anyone else.

32:22.105 --> 32:25.474
He didn't kill the guy
in the office, Clay.

32:25.844 --> 32:29.178
Yes, he did. You know
what I did was a mercy.

32:31.667 --> 32:34.335
I have a life
in Toronto.

32:34.618 --> 32:38.087
- A good life. It's my life.
- Keep telling yourself that.

32:40.357 --> 32:42.224
You'll find whoever
made the Mutt.

32:42.226 --> 32:44.393
Okay? You'll punish him.
But you don't need me!

32:44.395 --> 32:46.228
Keep telling
yourself that, too.

32:48.297 --> 32:51.002
He's not the only one
that needs you.

32:51.457 --> 32:53.597
We all do, Elena.

32:54.354 --> 32:56.654
This isn't what I need.

33:00.441 --> 33:04.877
I'm going home in the morning,
and I'm not coming back.

33:04.879 --> 33:07.695
Just take care of him,
Jeremy, okay?

33:07.921 --> 33:16.214
( ♪ )

33:22.394 --> 33:31.394
( ♪ )

33:35.240 --> 33:38.909
♪ There's a place ♪

33:38.911 --> 33:42.645
♪ That I've found ♪

33:42.647 --> 33:46.149
♪ Full of sins

33:46.151 --> 33:49.552
♪ That you've drowned ♪

33:49.553 --> 33:54.991
♪ I'll be your river ♪

33:54.994 --> 33:59.228
If my girlfriend catches you here,
I'm going to be in big trouble.

33:59.230 --> 34:08.230
( ♪ )

34:11.510 --> 34:15.873
- Is she the jealous type?
- She's completely unreasonable.

34:16.614 --> 34:18.946
How selfish of her.

34:19.750 --> 34:22.112
She's insatiable.

34:22.360 --> 34:23.760
(Clattering of belt)

34:23.761 --> 34:25.927
- And acrobatic.
- Uh-oh.

34:26.290 --> 34:29.891
Most days it's like the
Russian circus around here.

34:30.206 --> 34:32.438
You poor thing.

34:49.245 --> 34:51.679
(Panting)

34:55.051 --> 34:57.085
Feels good
to be home.

34:57.087 --> 35:04.725
( ♪ )

35:04.727 --> 35:07.061
Philip: I think it
should be called that...

35:07.063 --> 35:08.963
Why not?

35:08.965 --> 35:12.113
I think your neighbours can hear
everything that we're doing.

35:12.114 --> 35:16.399
Yeah, that would explain the high-fives
I get in the lobby every morning.

35:16.425 --> 35:17.371
(Laughter)

35:17.372 --> 35:19.331
Enough bragging
and start cooking.

35:19.332 --> 35:22.121
- Ahh, wow, dinner now too, huh?
- Yep.

35:22.123 --> 35:23.956
I'm a slave to
your appetites.

35:23.958 --> 35:26.626
Come on. (Clapping)
Chop chop.

35:26.628 --> 35:28.628
All right.

35:31.398 --> 35:33.615
See? This is what I needed.

35:34.060 --> 35:35.901
Some alone
time with you.

35:41.541 --> 35:42.908
(Giggles)

35:46.512 --> 35:48.013
Ooh, smells good.

35:48.015 --> 35:49.215
(Knocking on door)

35:49.217 --> 35:53.449
Oh, I completely forgot to tell you
we're having company over tonight.

35:54.555 --> 35:56.221
- Hi.
- Hi.

35:56.223 --> 35:58.666
You look surprised.

35:58.861 --> 36:00.328
I am.

36:00.329 --> 36:02.527
We ran into each other
at a coffee shop the other day,

36:02.529 --> 36:04.663
and I thought we should
have them over for dinner.

36:04.665 --> 36:06.446
Come on in.

36:06.586 --> 36:08.218
Let there be wine.

36:09.603 --> 36:12.136
- (Whispering) Really?
- I got blindsided too.

36:13.980 --> 36:16.215
Okay...

36:16.216 --> 36:18.209
Cousin. Car accident.

36:18.211 --> 36:19.701
Coma. Kids.

36:19.709 --> 36:23.114
- She's out of the woods.
- Okay. What name did you give her?

36:23.116 --> 36:24.827
I didn't.

36:24.828 --> 36:27.342
Philip: Hey, let
him in the door!

36:31.222 --> 36:34.212
- Logan.
- It's been too long. (Hands slapping)

36:35.060 --> 36:38.462
Antonio: Jeremy, really, it's no hardship
to stay on another night or two.

36:38.464 --> 36:42.666
The townspeople got their wolf.
Those hunters won't come back.

36:42.668 --> 36:45.468
Maybe it's time
we canvassed all the Mutts.

36:45.470 --> 36:47.905
Remind them why it's best
to follow the rules.

36:47.907 --> 36:50.207
That's a very good
idea, my friend.

36:50.209 --> 36:52.675
But that is a project
for tomorrow.

36:55.871 --> 36:57.604
I'm going for a run.

37:03.290 --> 37:05.301
He thought
she was gonna stay.

37:06.653 --> 37:08.386
So did I.

37:13.731 --> 37:16.365
I can't believe we haven't
done this before.

37:16.367 --> 37:19.498
Well, it's routines, you know?
We get stuck in them like train tracks.

37:19.499 --> 37:20.937
I like my routine.

37:20.939 --> 37:25.014
It's too bad that it takes something
awful for people to get together.

37:25.926 --> 37:27.967
Who's taking care
of the kids?

37:29.513 --> 37:30.846
Your cousin's kids.

37:30.848 --> 37:34.883
Well, now that Danielle
is awake, her husband's home.

37:34.885 --> 37:38.186
Yeah. Boys? Girls?
You never said.

37:38.188 --> 37:42.057
One of each. They're very young.
Um, four and six.

37:42.059 --> 37:45.494
Yeah, they haven't seen Danielle
in the hospital yet. Maybe soon.

37:45.496 --> 37:49.954
(Laugh) Funny, I mean... I've never heard
you talk about women in the family.

37:49.955 --> 37:52.447
- Other than Elena.
- Country cousins.

37:52.448 --> 37:55.816
I'm not even actually sure
how we're related to them.

37:56.854 --> 37:58.890
Who found who?

37:59.740 --> 38:01.111
I'm sorry?

38:01.112 --> 38:03.179
She didn't know about you
guys when she was growing up,

38:03.180 --> 38:05.913
and you didn't know
about her, so...

38:06.294 --> 38:07.694
Who found who?

38:07.696 --> 38:10.025
Rachel: The funny thing is that...
they didn't know about Logan, either.

38:10.026 --> 38:13.021
I mean, not until
you were, what, 16?

38:13.284 --> 38:15.174
What? You were in the
foster system too?

38:15.175 --> 38:17.238
No, I was raised
by my mother.

38:17.239 --> 38:19.332
- We're connected through my father.
- Right.

38:19.505 --> 38:21.998
But we're all together now.
One big happy family.

38:22.446 --> 38:26.978
That must have been so weird, finding out
that you have actual family out there.

38:26.979 --> 38:28.945
Yeah, it was weird.

38:29.304 --> 38:31.339
I'm still adjusting,
you know?

38:42.126 --> 38:44.883
- We're leaving tonight?
- I should head back to the city.

38:44.884 --> 38:46.747
(Exhaling)

38:46.773 --> 38:50.734
Clay is in full brood in the nude.
Maybe I should stay here.

38:50.736 --> 38:53.871
I think this is something that Jeremy
wants to handle in his own way.

38:53.873 --> 38:56.150
Besides, we've got another
issue to deal with.

38:56.151 --> 38:57.840
- Marsten.
- Exactly.

38:57.842 --> 38:59.842
I don't like the fact
that he was so close by.

38:59.844 --> 39:01.511
It was like he was
waiting for our call.

39:01.513 --> 39:03.444
He sure knows how to sniff out
an opportunity.

39:03.445 --> 39:04.617
And money.

39:04.618 --> 39:07.238
You and I are gonna follow
his financial tracks.

39:07.239 --> 39:09.834
See what he's up to.
All right. Get your stuff.

39:11.922 --> 39:15.919
So... Professional
opinion on the lasagna?

39:15.920 --> 39:19.364
Uh... no. I'm just happy whenever
anybody else does the cooking.

39:19.365 --> 39:21.479
- I don't critique.
- Right.

39:21.480 --> 39:24.328
I thought it was a little salty, too.
(Laughter)

39:24.329 --> 39:28.919
If Logan can get the Chinese food out of
the carton and onto a plate, I'm amazed.

39:30.507 --> 39:32.774
How are you two doing?

39:32.776 --> 39:35.811
Logan doesn't
really say much.

39:35.813 --> 39:39.181
I've... (Laugh) got
these crazy hours.

39:39.183 --> 39:41.150
You know, prepping the
kitchen at 9:00 a.m.,

39:41.152 --> 39:44.253
not getting home until 1:00
in the morning at the earliest.

39:44.255 --> 39:47.288
Never made for easy
relationships. But...

39:47.290 --> 39:50.459
Logan... I don't know,
he... gets it.

39:50.461 --> 39:54.863
- He gives me room.
- And you give him room.

39:54.865 --> 39:59.334
Yeah. But... now I'm curious
about the rest of his family.

39:59.336 --> 40:01.936
I don't know. They're
not what you'd expect.

40:01.938 --> 40:06.740
For a while there, I felt...
I don't know, like I was at home.

40:06.742 --> 40:10.528
But I couldn't shake the feeling
that I was just a visitor.

40:11.114 --> 40:12.680
I get that.

40:12.682 --> 40:15.590
But it's good to know there's
somebody there, right?

40:16.986 --> 40:18.597
Yeah.

40:26.282 --> 40:29.538
Tell me something, and
if I'm prying, I'll back off.

40:29.539 --> 40:32.819
But is everything
okay with Elena?

40:34.544 --> 40:35.744
Uh...

40:37.626 --> 40:40.327
What makes you
think it isn't?

40:40.329 --> 40:43.731
She has a hard time opening up,
and I never push her,

40:43.733 --> 40:48.004
but she's shared enough of her past that
I know she's holding in a lot of hurt.

40:48.571 --> 40:53.307
Well, and it really isn't
my place to say, but...

40:53.309 --> 40:57.034
I see you two together,
the way you make her laugh.

40:58.449 --> 41:02.283
You bring out the best side of her.
Just keep doing that.

41:02.787 --> 41:04.286
Look at me.

41:04.288 --> 41:07.722
I invite a psychologist to dinner
and I put him to work.

41:07.724 --> 41:09.558
Ah, don't worry about it.
I'm used to it.

41:09.560 --> 41:12.977
You know most doctors get canvassed
for giving off-hours advice.

41:13.297 --> 41:16.759
Except proctologists, right?
They're probably safe.

41:16.927 --> 41:18.806
You would hope so.

41:19.703 --> 41:20.903
(Laugh)

41:28.077 --> 41:29.610
(Ominous ♪)

41:29.612 --> 41:32.580
Philip: What do you think?
Coffee or scotch?

41:32.582 --> 41:34.515
Well, they go together,
don't they?

41:34.517 --> 41:36.317
(Chuckle)

41:36.319 --> 41:40.155
- Let's introduce them.
- All right, then.

41:40.157 --> 41:42.690
(Cellphone ringtone)

41:42.692 --> 41:44.192
That's our cousin.

41:46.901 --> 41:48.435
Clay.

41:54.492 --> 41:56.233
Uh...

41:57.209 --> 41:58.911
Okay.

41:59.787 --> 42:01.434
I, uh...

42:02.477 --> 42:04.044
I understand.

42:11.886 --> 42:14.321
Yeah, yeah, I know.
We-we can, of course.

42:14.322 --> 42:16.326
- No, I just...
- What is it?

42:16.327 --> 42:18.236
Another Danvers
called you.

42:18.237 --> 42:20.493
- Yeah, I'll tell her.
- A... Clayton?

42:20.495 --> 42:24.063
She's here with me now.
We're on our way.

42:27.255 --> 42:30.757
- Logan.
- It's not good.

42:30.759 --> 42:32.874
We have to go back.

42:34.049 --> 42:36.019
We have to go back
right away.

42:38.666 --> 42:40.906
He's not wearing
his jacket.

42:42.337 --> 42:45.171
He always took it
off before a fight.

42:45.173 --> 42:49.942
( ♪ )

42:49.944 --> 42:54.047
<i>♪ In these arms... ♪</i>

42:54.049 --> 42:55.315
<i>♪ In these arms ♪</i>

42:55.317 --> 42:58.485
<i>♪ Are where you want to stay ♪</i>

42:58.487 --> 43:01.354
He didn't go down without
hurting someone.

43:01.356 --> 43:02.622
Who did this?

43:02.624 --> 43:08.394
